Learnt about AWS ECS
Learnt about Docker
Installed docker on local machine
Created simple flask application
Created Dockerfile with port EXPOSE to 3000
Build the Dockerfile and generated docker image and tested it whether it is running or not
Created AWS ECR registry and pushed the generated image to the ECR registry repository
Created ECS cluster
Created task definitions for the cluster with launch type EC2 and attached the image URI from ECR repository
Created services for the container
Updated the security groups with required ports
By using the public IP with required port we can see the application running